---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Bay Navigator - a community resource by Bay Tides."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>

        <p class="text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mb-8">
          Last updated: January 2, 2026
        </p>

        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Summary
          </h2>
          <div class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6">
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              We don't track you. We don't collect personal information. We don't use cookies for tracking. We don't sell any data. This site is open source so you can verify this yourself.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <strong>We do not collect personal information.</strong> Bay Navigator is designed to respect your privacy:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>No account creation required</li>
            <li>No cookies for tracking or advertising</li>
            <li>No analytics that identify individual users</li>
            <li>No collection of names, emails, or contact information</li>
            <li>No third-party trackers</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Local Storage
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            We use your browser's local storage to save preferences that stay on your device:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li><strong>Theme preference</strong> (light/dark mode)</li>
            <li><strong>Favorite programs</strong> (only in the mobile app)</li>
            <li><strong>Recent searches</strong> (only in the mobile app)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            This data never leaves your device and is not sent to any server.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Smart Assistant
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            The Smart Assistant feature uses Azure OpenAI to help you find programs. When you use it:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>Your questions are sent to our Azure Function to process your request</li>
            <li>We do not store your conversation history on our servers</li>
            <li>Conversations are not linked to any personal identifier</li>
            <li>Azure OpenAI processes the request and responses are returned directly to you</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Hosting and Infrastructure
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Bay Navigator is hosted on Microsoft Azure Static Web Apps. Standard server logs may include:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>IP addresses (for security and rate limiting)</li>
            <li>Browser type and operating system</li>
            <li>Pages visited and timestamps</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            These logs are used for security purposes only and are not used to identify or track individuals.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            External Links
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            Bay Navigator links to external websites for program information. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these external sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Mobile Apps
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Our mobile apps (iOS and Android) follow the same privacy principles:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 space-y-2 mb-6">
            <li>No account required</li>
            <li>Favorites and preferences stored locally on your device</li>
            <li>Optional crash reporting through Sentry (can be disabled)</li>
            <li>No advertising or tracking SDKs</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Open Source
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            Bay Navigator is open source. You can review our code at <a href="https://github.com/baytides/baynavigator">github.com/baytides/baynavigator</a> to verify our privacy practices.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Children's Privacy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            Bay Navigator does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. Since we don't collect personal information from any user, this applies universally.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Changes to This Policy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            If we make changes to this privacy policy, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top. Significant changes will be announced on our GitHub repository.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">
            Contact
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-6">
            If you have questions about this privacy policy, you can contact us at hello [at] baytides [dot] org or open an issue on <a href="https://github.com/baytides/baynavigator/issues">GitHub</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12">
          <a href="/" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"/>
            </svg>
            Back to Programs
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
